"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458061","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-10","<p>The Attorney General's advice informed my decision to target Reyaad Khan. The strike was conducted by the RAF using rules of engagement informed by the Attorney General's advice.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-03-10T17:49:22.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458061/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458061/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458061/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-07","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Prime Minister's statement of 7 September 2015, Official Report, column 23, what rank of officer within the RAF chain of command had access to the Attorney General's advice on the legal basis for the Reyaad Khan drone strike.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","30084"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458062","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-10","<p>I refer the right hon. Member to the answer I gave on 23 November 2015 to Question 16741. It remains the case that provisions set out in the UK-US Memorandum of Understanding have not yet been enacted by either party.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-03-10T15:58:47.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458062/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458062/answer","Hansard Extract  23 November 2015  HOC 16741.docx","Syria Military Intervention","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458062/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-03-07","Unmanned Air Vehicles: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, in how many operations the UK Reaper force has transferred operational control of UK Reapers to (a) the US Air Force and (b) embedded RAF personnel in the US Air Force in Syria and Iraq since 2 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr David Davis","Haltemprice and Howden","Mr David Davis","30085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458063","Department for Education","false","2016-03-10","<p>Exam boards are independent organisations and the department continues to work closely with them to secure the future of all the existing GCSEs and A levels in less-taught languages, including Bengali.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-03-10T11:13:50.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458063/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458063/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458063/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-03-07","Bengali Language: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will require the Oxford, Cambridge and RSA, AQA and Edexcel examinations boards to offer GCSE and A-level Bengali examinations beyond September 2018; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","30083"
