"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458161","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-15","<p>The Government is continuing to actively consider how best to address problems wheelchair users face when using taxis and private hire vehicles, including the possible commencement of Section 165 of the Equality Act 2010.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-03-15T13:58:16.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458161/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458161/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458161/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-03-07","Taxis: Wheelchairs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 27 January 2016 to Question 23178, what recent progress the Government has made on planning to enact section 165 of the Equality Act 2010 on alternative means of ensuring that wheelchair users are able to access taxis.","false","Biography information for Karen Lumley","Redditch","Karen Lumley","30046"
