"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458167","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-11","<p>For schemes that are Open for Traffic, the actual out-turn costs have been provided. Schemes that are in development or construction show the latest approved estimate.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Scheme Name</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Announced</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Estimated Cost (£m)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Source of Estimate</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>M60 J8 to M62J20:Smart Motorway</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>228</p></td><td><p>Under construction</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>A556 Knutsford to Bowdon</p></td><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>191.9</p></td><td><p>Under construction</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>M6 J16 to J19</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>223.3</p></td><td><p>Under construction</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>For the remaining schemes outlined in the 1 December 2014 announcement, the current costs are the cost category as quoted in the RIS Investment Plan, which can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/381496/roads-investment-strategy-summary-of-schemes.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/381496/roads-investment-strategy-summary-of-schemes.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>There is currently no cost information for the Strategic Studies as they are in the very early stages of investigating options.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-03-11T12:09:49.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458167/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458167/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458167/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-03-07","Roads: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the most recent cost estimate is for each of the road projects listed in the Government's announcement, Major roads investment in the North West, published on 1 December 2014, that have not yet been completed; and what the final costs were of any of those projects that have been completed.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","29958"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458168","Department for Transport","false","2016-03-10","<p>Highways England is leading on the full and permanent reinstatement of the A591 and has committed to have the road fully reopened to the public by the end of May 2016.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-03-10T16:36:45.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458168/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458168/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/458168/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-03-07","A591: Cumbria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he expects the A591 in Cumbria to be fully accessible.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","29984"
